00:00:00.680 --> 00:00:04.730
&gt;&gt; From the Library of
Congress in Washington, DC.

00:00:18.360 --> 00:00:20.440
&gt;&gt; Steve Winick: Again,
my name is Steve Winick.

00:00:20.440 --> 00:00:23.080
I'm the editor here at the
American Folklife Center.

00:00:23.080 --> 00:00:26.820
Actually my job title is
writer/editor and that comes

00:00:26.820 --> 00:00:30.410
into play in the next thing
that I'm going to introduce,

00:00:30.410 --> 00:00:35.350 position:56%
which is the new edition of Folklife
and Fieldwork, which I think many

00:00:35.350 --> 00:00:38.460
of you have been handed
out on your way in.

00:00:38.460 --> 00:00:40.360
If you haven't, just
wave to a staff member

00:00:40.360 --> 00:00:43.900
and someone will approach
you and hand you a copy.

00:00:43.900 --> 00:00:47.720
But this is our fieldwork
manual and it has been

00:00:47.720 --> 00:00:49.170
around for a good long time.

00:00:49.170 --> 00:00:51.100
And in fact, the first
edition of Folklife

00:00:51.100 --> 00:00:54.690 position:56%
and Fieldwork was published in 1979.

00:00:54.690 --> 00:00:59.220
And the author of that book was
Peter Bartis, who we are very lucky

00:00:59.220 --> 00:01:03.900
to still have on the staff of the
American Folklife Center today.

00:01:03.900 --> 00:01:08.340
And Peter and I were the co-authors
of this new version of the book.

00:01:08.340 --> 00:01:13.630 position:56%
And so, I just want to talk a little
bit about what's new in the book,

00:01:13.630 --> 00:01:15.210
and also talk a little
bit about the history.

00:01:15.210 --> 00:01:17.540
I think one of the nice things
about Peter and I being able

00:01:17.540 --> 00:01:21.250
to collaborate on this is that
Peter was kind of an early student

00:01:21.250 --> 00:01:25.360
and I was kind of a later student
of a man named Kenny Goldstein.

00:01:25.360 --> 00:01:29.040 position:56%
And Kenny Goldstein's dissertation
was called "A Guide for Fieldworkers

00:01:29.040 --> 00:01:31.570
in Folklore", which
he then published

00:01:31.570 --> 00:01:35.520
through his own publishing company
and it was the fieldwork guide

00:01:35.520 --> 00:01:40.070
in folklore for years until, you
know, the sort of reflexivity

00:01:40.070 --> 00:01:43.750 position:56%
of looking at fieldwork became more
and more a thing within anthropology

00:01:43.750 --> 00:01:46.610
and ethnography, and then a lot
of books on fieldwork came out.

00:01:46.610 --> 00:01:49.870 position:56%
But before that was the case, if you
wanted to know much about fieldwork,

00:01:49.870 --> 00:01:51.370
you went to Kenny's book.

00:01:51.370 --> 00:01:56.070 position:56%
And so the fact that Peter distilled
a lot of the wisdom that he gotten

00:01:56.070 --> 00:02:00.000
from Kenny and that I then got
to rework some of this as well

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:02.370
in this new edition was very
nice for both of us I think

00:02:02.370 --> 00:02:06.330 position:56%
to acknowledge Kenny's effect on us.

00:02:06.330 --> 00:02:09.180
So what's new in the new edition
of Folklife and Fieldwork?

00:02:09.180 --> 00:02:11.530
It's always been a great guide,

00:02:11.530 --> 00:02:13.590
introductory guide on
how to do fieldwork.

00:02:13.590 --> 00:02:17.160
And I know that a lot of people
who worked on our field projects

00:02:17.160 --> 00:02:19.850
and then a lot of people
who've worked on field projects

00:02:19.850 --> 00:02:23.040
and field schools that we've
run have used the book.

00:02:23.040 --> 00:02:26.650
But we did make a few large
changes in the new edition.

00:02:26.650 --> 00:02:31.120
In particular, we decided to make
it a little bit more chronological

00:02:31.120 --> 00:02:35.100
so that we essentially
laid it out in the order

00:02:35.100 --> 00:02:36.860
in which you would
think about things

00:02:36.860 --> 00:02:38.600
when you're doing a
fieldwork project.

00:02:38.600 --> 00:02:41.720
So you have to think about the
ethics up in advance, right,

00:02:41.720 --> 00:02:43.540
before you actually
design the project,

00:02:43.540 --> 00:02:45.790
so that's up toward the
beginning of the book.

00:02:45.790 --> 00:02:50.290
So that made a big change in
the book from the old version.

00:02:50.290 --> 00:02:53.900
And one thing that's nice about
that is that it allows the table

00:02:53.900 --> 00:02:56.720
of contents to essentially be a
checklist of things that you have

00:02:56.720 --> 00:02:59.640
to do on the way to doing
a fieldwork project.

00:02:59.640 --> 00:03:04.130
So if you take a look at that,
you'll see that as one aspect

00:03:04.130 --> 00:03:06.150
of the new nature of the book.

00:03:06.150 --> 00:03:10.820
Second thing is that the tone
has gotten a little big lighter.

00:03:10.820 --> 00:03:14.190
We are hoping for a kind of a
broader audience, maybe to be able

00:03:14.190 --> 00:03:17.380
to use it with advance
undergraduate but also they use it

00:03:17.380 --> 00:03:20.280
with graduate students
and with professionals.

00:03:20.280 --> 00:03:23.040
And for that reason,
we adopted what I said

00:03:23.040 --> 00:03:25.330
in the early production
meeting, I used the word breezy

00:03:25.330 --> 00:03:28.090
and that became a kind
of a joke among us.

00:03:28.090 --> 00:03:31.510
So this is the breezy version
of Folklife and Fieldwork.

00:03:31.510 --> 00:03:35.710
And the third thing that
you'll notice is some issues

00:03:35.710 --> 00:03:38.010
that we weren't able to talk
about at length in the book

00:03:38.010 --> 00:03:40.340
but that we wanted to
introduce are brought

00:03:40.340 --> 00:03:43.830
up in these little green text
boxes and it's kind of interesting

00:03:43.830 --> 00:03:48.790
to hear a lot of the issues that
were brought up during the morning

00:03:48.790 --> 00:03:52.710
and see how we dealt with some of
them in Folklife and Fieldwork.

00:03:52.710 --> 00:03:55.490
So I'll say on page six, if
you want to flip to page six

00:03:55.490 --> 00:03:58.990
on the very bottom, there's
a green box that says,

00:03:58.990 --> 00:04:01.250
one of the first decisions
to make is whether

00:04:01.250 --> 00:04:03.920
to do your fieldwork
alone or in a team.

00:04:03.920 --> 00:04:07.060
Many of the best field projects in
the AFC archive were accomplished

00:04:07.060 --> 00:04:10.320
by teams of fieldworkers
rather than individuals.

00:04:10.320 --> 00:04:13.170
Teams allow you to divide the
labor, to document the process

00:04:13.170 --> 00:04:16.680 position:56%
of fieldwork, for example, by
photographing interviews in progress

00:04:16.680 --> 00:04:18.600
and to brainstorm with teammates.

00:04:18.600 --> 00:04:20.560
They also require you to negotiate

00:04:20.560 --> 00:04:23.690
with your teammates beginning right
here with the goals of the project.

00:04:23.690 --> 00:04:26.260
So again, we're putting that
in where you have to make

00:04:26.260 --> 00:04:28.220
that decision, which
is when you're thinking

00:04:28.220 --> 00:04:30.750
about what you actually
want to accomplish.

00:04:30.750 --> 00:04:36.980 position:56%
Another example is on page 11, when
we talk about the IRB and, you know,

00:04:36.980 --> 00:04:40.150
the issue that if you're
at a university you may run

00:04:40.150 --> 00:04:42.130
into this issue and you
have to be conscious of it.

00:04:42.130 --> 00:04:45.650 position:56%
So those are things that we try to
bring up this kind of both practical

00:04:45.650 --> 00:04:48.710
and theoretical and ethical
concerns that you might have

00:04:48.710 --> 00:04:52.020
and to bring them up in a way
that essentially directs you

00:04:52.020 --> 00:04:57.410 position:56%
to our website where we have larger
discussions of these issues for you.

00:04:57.410 --> 00:05:01.660
So that's one thing to
say about the new book.

00:05:01.660 --> 00:05:05.510
And then the other thing
is just that, you know,

00:05:05.510 --> 00:05:09.970
it's gotten a new design look
so that it's in color now.

00:05:09.970 --> 00:05:13.460
And we hope that that'll help
folks to interface with it.

00:05:13.460 --> 00:05:15.590
You know, it'll make it
sort of more eye-catching.

00:05:15.590 --> 00:05:17.240
So, that's Folklife and Fieldwork.

00:05:17.240 --> 00:05:21.620
It is now a physical book which you
can hold in your hands as you see.

00:05:21.620 --> 00:05:24.620
It's also a PDF which is going
up on our website as soon

00:05:24.620 --> 00:05:26.450
as we can make it accessible.

00:05:26.450 --> 00:05:30.050
So keep, you know, revisiting
our website and very soon,

00:05:30.050 --> 00:05:32.870
within the next couple of weeks,
we're going to have Folklife

00:05:32.870 --> 00:05:34.520
and Fieldwork up there as well.

00:05:34.520 --> 00:05:35.820
So now--

