00:39:26.610 --> 00:39:30.300
I wanted to document Baton Rouge.

00:39:30.300 --> 00:39:34.050
The larger project is now
called Baton Rouge Traditions.

00:39:34.050 --> 00:39:40.320
It's a small midsize southern
city that boom since World War II.

00:39:40.320 --> 00:39:44.570
Over the years I've noticed
that all too many people

00:39:44.570 --> 00:39:48.750
like to criticize Baton
Rouge, my hometown

00:39:48.750 --> 00:39:51.490
and Louisiana's capital city.

00:39:51.490 --> 00:39:55.660
People love the state and its
culture but some make an exception

00:39:55.660 --> 00:40:01.120
about Baton Rouge, especially
cultural workers and researchers.

00:40:01.120 --> 00:40:04.630
Many residents and
especially nonresidents think

00:40:04.630 --> 00:40:09.130
that it lacks any expressions of
folk culture even though it is home

00:40:09.130 --> 00:40:10.710
to an array of individuals

00:40:10.710 --> 00:40:14.470
who maintain Louisiana's
defining traditions.

00:40:14.470 --> 00:40:17.100
I started wondering why
Baton Rouge is perceived

00:40:17.100 --> 00:40:19.010
as having no folk culture.

00:40:19.010 --> 00:40:23.140
I knew that as the capital
city, it is a cultural microcosm

00:40:23.140 --> 00:40:26.550
with people coming from
across the state to work.

00:40:26.550 --> 00:40:29.490
Others have moved here from
throughout the United States

00:40:29.490 --> 00:40:34.510
for employment at the
universities and industry.

00:40:34.510 --> 00:40:39.320
I began to realize that Baton
Rouge had a major identity issue.

00:40:39.320 --> 00:40:42.890
It doesn't help that Baton Rouge
is sandwiched between New Orleans

00:40:42.890 --> 00:40:48.300 position:56%
and Lafayette, two cities that are
known for their traditional culture.

00:40:48.300 --> 00:40:51.760
The rapid increase in
population coincide

00:40:51.760 --> 00:40:53.900
with the growth of suburbia.

00:40:53.900 --> 00:40:57.970 position:56%
The region includes urban, suburban,
and rural areas in addition

00:40:57.970 --> 00:41:02.230 position:56%
to small towns that are closely
connected to the city creating a web

00:41:02.230 --> 00:41:05.050
of relationships and networks.

00:41:05.050 --> 00:41:07.210
As the economic hub of the region,

00:41:07.210 --> 00:41:12.090
its population density allows
specialized businesses to exist

00:41:12.090 --> 00:41:15.830
that otherwise, would
be difficult to sustain.

00:41:15.830 --> 00:41:18.970
And thus, the Baton Rouge
Folklife survey was born.

